  "bio_raw": "Atanu Shuvam Roy is a highly skilled Computer Science and Engineering professional with a Master of Technology from the Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur (2022-2024), and a Bachelor of Engineering from Jiangxi University of Science & Technology (2018-2022). His extensive research experience at the IoT Vision Lab at IIT Kanpur and the Robotics and Automation Research Lab (RARL) focuses on\nDeep Learning, Computer Vision, IoT, and Robotics.\nHis key achievement includes optimizing YOLOv7 by integrating the Efficient Channel Attention (ECA) mechanism to detect water pipeline defects for the\nGovernment of India's Jal Jeevan Mission project\n, successfully reducing the\nmodel's parameters by 20%\n. He has also developed a streetlight management system using FMCW RADAR and LoRaWAN which served as a prototype for RADAR based object detection. He has been working on energy-aware AGV path planning in recent times. He supplements his research background with industry experience as a\nWeb Developer & DevOps Engineer\nat Backend Ace and an Associate Web Developer at Wizzartech. He is a prolific contributor, credited with\n12 publications\nin venues like\nIEEE Access\nand\nVISAPP 2024\n, and is proficient in\nPython, JavaScript (NodeJS/ReactJS), PyTorch, and Flutter.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Embedded Systems, Robotics & Automation, Computer Vision, Internet of Things (IoT), Automated Guided Vehicles."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMaster of Technology (MTech)\nin Computer Science & Engineering\nIndian Institute of Technology Kanpur"
    }
  ],
